The HTML code you've provided is not entirely accessible as there are several issues:

1. **Closing Bracket Missing**: The div with `id="section-top-promo-1"` is missing a closing bracket, which creates an imbalance in the HTML structure.

2. **Role and ID Confusion**: The `<span>` element with `id="searchSubmitButton"` and `role="search"` is misplaced in relation to the `<form>` tag. It should be part of the form or directly associated with the form element.

3. **CSS Classes and IDs**: There are potential issues with the CSS classes and IDs. For instance, `top-space-none` and `gradient-bottom-border` are not standard CSS classes or IDs. They might be custom classes, but ensure they are correctly defined in your CSS.

4. **Inline Styles**: The inline styles are not necessary for the accessibility or the visual presentation of your form. It might be better to apply these styles via CSS classes.

5. **Semantic Elements**: The HTML document does not start (`<html>`) and end (`</html>`), which is necessary for a complete HTML file.

Here's a corrected version of the code, assuming you're trying to create an accessible form:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Search Form</title>
    <style>
        /* Add your CSS styles here */
        .gradient-bottom-border {
            background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, #00629B, transparent);
            /* Add other styles */
        }

        .top-space-md {
            /* Add styles */
        }

        .left-right-space-sm {
            /* Add styles */
        }

        .container-fluid {
            /* Add styles */
        }

        /* Other styles */
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <form action="/searchresults/index.html" role="search" id="searchForm">
        <span class="input-group-addon" id="searchSubmitButton">
            <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-search"></i>
        </span>
        <div id="section-top-promo-1" class="gradient-bottom-border top-space-none left-right-space-sm container-fluid" style="background-color: transparent;">
            <!-- Add form fields here -->
        </div>
    </form>
</body>
</html>
```

Please note that you should replace the comment `<!-- Add form fields here -->` with your actual form fields, such as `input` elements for search terms and possibly a submit button. Also, ensure that your CSS styles are correctly defined, and consider using ARIA labels if you need to improve accessibility further.

